<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A NSW prison guard is accused of smuggling tobacco and two mobile phone chargers into a jail on the state's mid north coast.</p>

<p>Last month, detectives from the Corrective Services Investigation Unit established Strike Force Acres to investigate the introduction of contraband by the female officer.</p>

<p>Detectives arrested a 49-year-old woman at a Port Macquarie home on Tuesday.</p>

<p>A NSW prison guard is accused of smuggling tobacco and two mobile phone chargers into a jail on the state's mid north coast (file picture)</p>

<p>She was taken to Port Macquarie Police Station and charged with unlawfully secreting a thing for an inmate to receive.</p>

<p>Police will allege in court that the woman, who is a Corrective Services NSW officer, trafficked tobacco and two mobile phone chargers into a correctional facility in July this year.</p>

<p>The woman was granted strict conditional bail to appear at Port Macquarie Local Court on October 14.</p>

<p>The woman has been suspended by Corrective Services NSW.</p>
